    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-09T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-09T21:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1020: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative of the President</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-09T20:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 9, 1937—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 10—12:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Referring to the Department’s telegram of December 7, point regarding stamps
                    has been eliminated and both delegations are ready to sign tomorrow afternoon at
                    5 o’clock. The accepted draft takes points 1 to 7 of the Honduran note No. 12
                    (refer to enclosure to my despatch No. 25 of November 27th<note n="61"
                        xml:id="d129fn61">Not printed.</note>) almost verbatim. Point 8 in
                    translation now reads “A mutual offer of both Governments not to solve the
                    present conflict by means of arms.” Point No. 9 (final point) “A mutual offer of
                    both Governments to solve the present conflict by pacific means as established
                    by international law.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
